Package: pedprobr
Type: Package
Title: Pedigree Probabilities in R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Magnus Dehli", "Vigeland", 
                  email = "m.d.vigeland@medisin.uio.no", 
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A reboot of the computational heart of the retired paramlink
    package, implementing the Elston-Stewart algorithm for calculating pedigree 
    likelihoods. It is part of a suite of packages for pedigree analysis in R, 
    using pedtools as the foundational package for handling pedigrees and 
    markers.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.1.0)
Imports: pedtools,
    pedmut
Suggests: testthat
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
